15. dxc5! {[%mdl 32768]} { A very rare move but a really strong one. } Rf8+ ( { It makes sense to bring the rook to the game first. } 15...Qxg4 { leads to a difficult endgame: } 16.Nf4 Qxd1+ 17.Rxd1 Bxc3 18.Nd5 Bf6 19.Nxf6+ exf6 20.Rd7 $16 { 17...Nc4 is not any better: 18.Bf2 Bxc3 19.Rd7 Nd2+ 20.Ke2 Nxe4 21.Nd5 $16 with great winning chances. }) 
16. Kg1 Qxg4 
17. Qd5+! {[%cal Re7e6]} ( { An important intermezzo - provoking ...e6 helps White. } 17.Qd3 Qe6! { is also better for White, but less clear. } ) e6 
18. Qd3 $16  { White has an extra pawn and Black does not have any compensation here. } *

