14. Qh3 Ne7 
15. Bg5 Ng6 
16. Bxf6 gxf6 
17. Rad1 {[%cal Gd4d5,Rh3d7,Gd3e4]} { Pushing d5 is already a threat thanks to the pressure on the h3-d7 diagonal. White's main idea is Be4 to trade bishops and bring the knight over to the kingside. } Rad8 
18. Be4 {[%cal Ge4b7,Gb7e4,Gc3e4]} -- ( { There are other options, too, but I think that this is the most challenging. White wants to trade bishops to bring the knight to the kingside, and you can see here [/variation/21474153/#/19/w] how that works out for us. } 18...f5 { stops that idea but runs into } 19.Bxb7 Qxb7 20.d5 $14 { with a favorable transformation in the structure. } )
