18. Kg1 {[%mdl 32768]} ( 18.e6 { is an option, but } 18...Qf6!= { is strong and Black equalizes here nicely, as Peter showed. } ) Rf8! ( { Bringing the final piece into the game. } 18...Bxe5?! 19.Qd3 $14 ) 
19. Bh4! ( { One of the good tries for White. } 19.Bd4 Bxe5 { is just nothing for White. } ) Ne3 
20. e6! Qxe6 
21. Qb3 Nc4! ( { This is the recommendation of Peter Svidler. Engines initially give White some edge and I was happy about it at first, but looking at it deeper I realized that there is not much. } 21...Qxb3?! 22.axb3 $14 { fixes White's pawn structure and I think Black is worse here. } ) 
22. Nd4 Qd5 { White has some choice here. } 
