12. h4!? {[%mdl 32768]} { A typical idea in these positions, but again, after the queen moved to c7, h4 acquires additional strength as ...e5 or ...e6 does not allow the queen to go to the kingside. } e5?! { This move, in connection with Rd8, makes sense but still is not sufficiently good enough. White is better in many ways. } 
13. d5 Na5 
14. Bd3 { Is also better for White. } f5 ( 14...b6 15.h5 { is clearly better for White. } ) 
15. exf5! gxf5 
16. Bg5! -- ( { Black would lose an exchange in the event of 16...Rxd5, but alternatives are hardly any better. } 16...Rxd5 17.Bc4 Nxc4 18.Qxd5+ Qf7 19.Qd8+ Qf8 20.Rcd1 $16 { 16...Rf8 17.Ng3 $16 } )
