23. h3 Qd7 
24. d6 bxc4 
25. Bb4 $13  { Finally, the position stabilized. It is approximately equal. But Black needs to find really lots of good moves on the way to reach it. And even if they do, the game goes on. In this position, White may try to trade dark-squared bishops and make use of highly advanced d-pawn. There is a chance that White's knight will become pretty good, especially with dark-squared bishops off the board. } *

