17. Bg5! {[%cal Gd4d5,Gh2h4,Gg5e7]} { I think that this looks promising, even if objectively Black should be fine. Apart from the Be7 threat, White's two main ideas are d5 and h4-h5. They both look kind of scary. Black has many moves available here but the position remains playable. } a6 ( { We are following the game Giri-Nepomniachtchi (2021). } 17...Bxe4? 18.Be7 $16 ) 
18. Bd3 Nc6 
19. Bb1 {[%mdl 32768]} Qd7 
20. h4! {[%cal Gh4h5]} { Launching a typical initiative on the kingside. The position remains playable and I like White's chances here. } Rc8 ( 20...h5? 21.e5! $16 ) 
21. h5 Na5 { Black should look for some active counterplay. But playing first ...Nc6, and now ...Na5-Nc4 back again is not intuitive at all. } 
22. h6 Nc4 
23. Qf4 Bf8 
24. d5!? { I think that this is quite challenging for Black. } exd5 
25. exd5 -- ( { And after } 25...Nd6 { White can play either } 26.Bf6!? Rc4 27.Qd2 Qg4 28.Ba1 Bxd5 29.Ng3 { or } { 26.Ng3!? Rc4 27.Qd2 and in both cases White's chances are better. } )
*

