7. bxc3!? {[%mdl 32768]} ( { I think that this is the most challenging, even if slightly surprising. } 7.Nxc3 { is simpler and also better for White, but I just think that 7.bxc3 is more promising. Here, Black can try } 7...exd4 8.exd4 d5! { (better than 8...Nxd4? 9.O-O O-O 10.Bg5 $16 ) } 9.Be3 O-O 10.O-O Nb4 { with some resistance. } ) e4 ( { Otherwise, White will play e4 with big advantage. } 7...d6? 8.e4 O-O 9.O-O $16 { is similar to positions discussed after 4...Bxc3. } ) 
8. Bc2 Na5 
9. c5! {[%cal Ge1g1,Gf2f3]} { No reason to give away the pawn. Next, White wants to undermine the center via f3. } d5 
10. cxd6 cxd6 
11. O-O d5 
12. f3! { A typical way to undermine the center. } exf3 
13. gxf3 $14  {[%cal Ge3e4]} { And e4 is coming soon. } *

