14. Qe2 $14  {[%cal Gd4d5,Rd4c5]} { White has some edge here due to the strong center and well-placed pieces. There are many possible plans and ideas here. One of them is to play at some point d5 and build get a strong passed pawn, a typical idea in the Grunfeld (this position sort of resembles Grunfeld, doesn't it?) or something along the lines with dxc5 where White begin to play against Black's weakened c5-pawn. } *

