17. Rae1 {[%cal Ge3e4]} Ne7! ( { A strong move played in Shankland-Sanikidze (2016). Everything else is much worse. However, I believe that Black still does not equalize. } 17...h4?! 18.Nh1 h3 19.Ng3! $16 { followed by e4 is great for White. } ) 
18. e4 {[%mdl 32768]} h4 
19. Nh1 Ng6? { Sanikidze erred with the text move. } 
20. e5 $16  { Puts Black under big pressure. } Nh5 ( { Mistakes come together, as the saying goes... } 20...Nh7 { was forced, but still, White is much better. } 21.f4 f5 22.g4!? $16 ) 
21. Bc1! {[%cal Gf3f4][%csl Rh4]} -- ( { With a winning position as f4 comes, or Black loses the h4-pawn as in the game: } 21...Nhf4 22.Bxf4 Nxf4 23.Qxh4 Nd3 24.Re3 Re6 25.f4+- { Shankland-Sanikidze (2016). } )
