14. Bd6! Red8! { The best move, but hard to play I think. } 
15. c5 bxc5 
16. Rb1!? ( { Here, White has two options, } 16. Rb1.15...Ne8 ) ( 16.Bxa6 Qxa6 17.Be7 Nxe5 18.dxe5 Rd7 19.Bd6 $14 { is also not fully equal. } ) Qc8 
17. Bxa6 ( 17.Nxd7!? Bxd3 18.Nxf6+ gxf6 19.Qxd3 c4 20.Qe2 Rxd6 21.e4 { with long-term compensation, but objectively equal. } ) Qxa6 
18. Nxd7 Rxd7 
19. dxc5 { This line could be unpleasant for Black too. } *

