1. d4 Nf6 
2. c4 e6 
3. Nc3 Bb4 
4. e3 { The Rubinstein Variation in Nimzo Indian is one of the oldest and the most tested in practice classical approaches in this opening. Developed in the early 1900s by the top players of that era, popularized mainly by Rubinstein and his e3-Ne2 idea (the Rubinstein Variation in its purest form), these days it went through well-scrutinized analysis by modern top players with the support of best engines.

Over the years many variations were tested and tried. With such a strategically sound opening like Nimzo, it is pretty much impossible to find an objective advantage if Black plays sound lines. And it is neither my objective to refute 100+ years of theory that Stockfish and Lc0 support. But finding playable positions that pose some practical problems for players who are not thoroughly familiar with the ideas is highly possible. } c5 
5. Nge2 cxd4 
6. exd4 {[%mdl 32768]} O-O 
7. a3 Bxc3+ { Giving the bishop pair without an option of getting an isolated pawn position with ...dxc4, cannot be good for Black. } 
8. Nxc3 d5 
9. c5! {[%csl Ga3,Gb2,Gc5,Gd4]} { Gaining space on the queenside. } Nc6 
10. Bb5 e5 ( { The best chance for Black is to react in the center. } 10...Ne4 11.O-O Nxc3 12.bxc3 Qa5 { 12...Bd7 13.Bf4 $16 } 13.Bxc6 bxc6 14.Bf4 $16 ) 
11. dxe5 Nxe5 
12. Bf4! { Black is definitely under pressure. There is no ...Re8 which is pretty important. } d4 ( { Black needs to give up a pawn and try to defend a difficult middlegame or endgame. } 12...Ng6? 13.Bd6+- ) ( 12...Nc4? 13.O-O Nxb2 { here White has many good options. } 14.Qc1 Nc4 15.Bxc4 dxc4 16.Rd1 Qa5 17.Be5!+- { is rather convincing. } ) 
13. Bxe5 dxc3 { Here, White has several good options. } 
14. O-O!? ( 14.Qxd8 Rxd8 15.Bxc3 Ne4 16.Rc1 $14 { White is better in the endgame. } ) ( 14.Bxc3 { surprisingly gives Black a lot of counterplay: } 14...Nd5! 15.Qd4 Nxc3 16.Qxc3 a6! 17.Ba4 Qh4 18.b4 Qe4+ ) cxb2 
15. Bxb2 $14  { Perhaps this is the easiest. The pair of bishops in the middlegame with pawns on both sides of the board should give White serious winning chances. } *

