15. Qd2 {[%mdl 32768]} Bg4 { This has been tried in two games so far, both won by Black. Objectively, however, White is better: } 
16. Bxd6! Rxd6 
17. Nf4 Qh6 
18. Bb5! {[%cal Gb5c6][%csl Ge1]} { Generally, White wants to trade on c6 and occupy the e-file, while trying to render Black's bishop useless. Tokhirjonova-Abrahamyan (2022) continued: } g5 
19. Ng2 Bf3 
20. Re3 ( 20.Bxc6!? { is also good. } 20...Rxc6 21.Re5 f6 22.Re3 Qh5 23.Ne1 Be4 24.Rc1 $14 ) Qf6 ( 20...g4 21.Nh4 Be4 22.h3 $14 { is slightly better for White too. } ) 
21. Bxc6 Rxc6 { And only here I would suggest a serious improvement. } 
22. Re5! ( 22.Rae1 { was played in the game but now } 22...Be4! { makes Black's bishop really powerful while the white rooks are awkward. } ) h6 
23. Ne3 $14  {[%cal Ge3d5,Ge3f5]} { With a clear edge. } *

