18. Qb5!? -- ( { I think White is slightly better due to the pair of bishops. It may not be that much objectively, but again, Black hasn't done anything terrible to offer White suddenly great winning chances. I think it should be easier to play with White. Play may continue } 18...Nf6 19.dxc5!? Rxd1+ 20.Rxd1 bxc5 21.Ba3 $14 { with a slight edge. } { I'll briefly show other possible continuations: 18...c4 19.Ba3 $14 or @@StartFEN@@2rr2k1/p1qn1ppp/1p6/1Qp1p3/P2Pb3/2P1P3/1B2BPPP/R2R2K1 b - - 0 18@@EndFEN@@ 18...Nf8 19.Bg4 Rb8 20.f3 Bc6 21.Qe2 $14 or @@StartFEN@@2rr2k1/p1qn1ppp/1p6/1Qp1p3/P2Pb3/2P1P3/1B2BPPP/R2R2K1 b - - 0 18@@EndFEN@@ 18...Qb7?! 19.f3! Bc6 20.Qa6 $14 with e4 next. All look good for White. } { On the other hand, 18.f3 c4! $13 , followed by ...Bc2, is not so clear. } )
