5. Bd2 b6 { The best alternative setup for Black. Let's see some alternatives: } ( { After } 5...d6 { our Bd2 is not that useful - it would be better to have Bd3 and Ne2 played, but it is also fine. } 6.Bd3 c5 { ( 6...e5 7.Nge2 $14 is not as perfect as the position with O-O instead of Bd2, but still very good.) } 7.Nge2 Nc6 8.O-O $14 { I am not sure if there is much to analyze... White is clearly better, thanks to our strong control over the center. } ) ( 5...c6 6.Nf3 d5 { the point of this move is that recapturing with ...cxd5 is possible. It transposes to 5...d5 6.Nf3 c6, which is inaccurate, as I discuss briefly. } ) 
