[Event "Lifetime Repertoires: Swiercz's 1. d4 - Part 1"]
[White "43) King's Indian: Be2-Be3 6...e5 7.d5 Na6 8.h4 & 10.h5"]
[Black "8...h5"]
[Date "2023.01.24"]
[Result "*"]
[SourceTitle "https://www.chessable.com/variation/21833058"]
[ECO "E73"]

1. d4 Nf6 
2. c4 g6 
3. Nc3 Bg7 
4. e4 d6 
5. Be2 O-O 
6. Be3 e5 
7. d5 { White should close the center. The benefit of having played Be2 and delaying Nf3 is that White now has additional options of kingside play, namely g4!? but also h4.

Typically, Black wants to play the ...f5 break, which now tougher - not only ...Nh5 is off the table, but very often White plays g4, stopping any ...f5. } Na6 {[%cal Ga6c5][%csl Re4]} { I consider this the most reasonable option for Black. The idea is to put quick pressure on the e4-pawn. } 
8. h4!? {[%mdl 32768]} { Not the most popular move here overall but it has recently gained some popularity and I think it puts a lot of pressure. } h5? {[%cal Gg1h3,Gh3g5,Yg2g4][%csl Gg5]} { This is, generally, good news for White. Now, ...f5 is unlikely, the g5-square can be potentially occupied by White's knight (Nh3-Ng5), and some g4 ideas could be in the cards (especially if Black's knight leaves f6) immediately undermining Black's kingside. Black is in trouble. } 
9. f3! {[%cal Gf3g4][%csl Rg4]} { Achieving a Saemisch-like setup. There are no ...Ng4 ideas anymore. } c6 ( 9...Nh7? 10.g4+- { . } ) 
10. Qd2 { It is hard to come up with an active plan for Black. } cxd5 ( 10...Nc5 { runs into } 11.b4 $16 { . } ) 
11. cxd5 Bd7 ( 11...Nc5 12.b4 Ncd7 13.Nh3 { is also great for White, e.g., } 13...a5 14.b5! b6 15.Na4+- { . } ) 
12. Nh3! {[%cal Gh3f2,Gg2g4,Yh3g5]} { With the idea of Ng5 or Nf2-g4. } Bxh3 ( 12...Qa5 { is met by } 13.Nf2!? { preparing g4. } )
13. Rxh3 { 13.Ng5 is also good, of course. 13...Rfc8 14.Rb1+- . } Nc5 
14. O-O-O!? {[%csl Gc1]} -- ( { The king is safe on the queenside. Black's position does not have much potential for active play without the light-squared bishop. White may switch to queenside play. A sample continuation is } 14...Rc8 15.Kb1 a6 16.Rhh1 b5 17.Rc1 $16 { . } )
