9. Qd2! { Full prophylaxis. White prevents ...f5 ideas as Bf4 will be defended and there are still issues with developing the queenside. Also, if ambitious, there are ideas of h4 and Bh6! } ( 9.Nf3 { can be played too, transposing to another line. However, Qd2 is even stronger. } ) a6 ( 9...f5 10.Nf3! fxe4 11.Nxe4+ { and the Bf4 is defended! } ) 
10. a4 Re8 
11. h3 $16  {[%cal Gh3g4,Gg1f3][%csl Rg4]} ( { Preventing ...Bg4 with Nf3 next. After } 11.Nf3 Bg4 { at least the bishop gets out! } ) *

