[ECO "A51"]

1. d4 Nf6 
2. c4 e5 
3. dxe5 {[%mdl 32768]} Ne4 ( { The Budapest is a risky opening choice for Black, but } 3...Ne4 { , Fajarowicz Variation, is even riskier. Historically it has been played many times but Stockfish pretty much just refutes it. } ) 
4. a3! { A strong prophylactic move. Black's main idea here is normally ...Bb4 and this move just kills it. } b6 { An interesting move with which Black tries to defend the knight with ...Bb7 and only later play ...d6. It also sets a devious but typical trap. } 
5. Nf3 ( { White should not capture the rook with } 5.Qd5 Nc5 6.Qxa8? { due to } 6...Bb7 7.Qxa7 Nc6 $17 { and the queen is trapped. } ) Bb7 
6. g3!? { I would recommend this line. There are very few games here but Stockfish likes it the most. The idea is to counter the Bb7 with Bg2. } Bc5 
7. e3 a5 ( 7...Ng5 { is easily parried by } 8.Bg2+- { . } ) 
8. Bg2 d6 { Here, there are many good options for White. I would like to suggest the most forcing one. } 
9. Nh4!? dxe5 
10. Qc2 Nd6 
11. Bxb7 Nxb7 
12. Qe4! c6 
13. Qxe5++- { With an extra pawn and winning position. } *

