9. Bd3 {[%mdl 32768]} { This is a playable alternative (and actually the main line according to the theory, or Bb5-Bd3 which is the same). } c5 ( { But not } 9...O-O? 10.e5 h6 11.h4! $16 { with the idea of Rh3-Rg3 and a strong attack on the kingside. } ) 
10. O-O ( 10.Bf4 { is possible too but right now Black can perhaps delay castling which gives some additional options while ...O-O is transposing to the main line. Therefore, with 9. Bf4 White reduces Black's options. } ) cxd4 
11. cxd4 O-O 
12. Bb2 Nc6 
13. a3 Rc8 
14. Qe2 $14  { This transposes to Queen's Indian Petrosian Variation (4.a3). Of course, this is also playable and engines like it too. } *

